ZCZC GE51
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
TUESDAY TO FRIDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 072300 UTC
DURING TUESDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE ACROSS SERN BRITAIN WILL
COLLAPSE SWARDS AS A LOW PRESSURE CENTRE 1012 NEAR ICELAND MOVS SWARDS ACROSS
THE BRITISH ISLES AND DEEPENS TO 1007. THE AZORES HIGH PRESSURE WILL THEN
EXTEND A RIDGE NWARDS TO ICELAND. THE LOW PRESSURE WILL CONTINUE TO DEEPEN
THROUGH THURSDAY TO 998 AS IT MOVS SWARDS TO FITZROY WHILE THE AREA OF HIGH
PRESSURE 1034 WILL BECOME CENTRED BETWEEN SCOTLAND AND ICELAND. A SIMILAR
PRESSURE PATTERN WILL PERSIST THROUGH FRIDAY WITH HIGH PRESSURE CENTRED E
OF ICELAND AND LOW PRESSURE 995 IN FITZROY. DURING TUESDAY EVENING SE WINDS
MAY BE OCNL STRG IN FAIR ISLE THEN THROUGH WEDNESDAY SE WINDS WILL BECOME
OCNL STRG MORE WIDELY IN THE N SEA. ON THURSDAY OCNL STRG WINDS WILL BECOME
NE WITH STRG WINDS EXTENDING TO THAMES DOVER AND WIGHT. SIMILAR STRENGTH
WINDS WILL PERSIST THROUGH FRIDAY
